==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palpitate
<hw>Pal"pi*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Palpitated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Palpitating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>palpitare</ets>, <ets>palpitatum</ets>, v. intens. fr.
<ets>pappare</ets>. See <er>Palpable</er>.]</ety> <def>To beat rapidly
and more strongly than usual; to throb; to bound with emotion or
exertion; to pulsate violently; to flutter; -- said specifically of the
heart when its action is abnormal, as from excitement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>palpitating</ent>⟦br⟧
